verbs.description: concretize (third-person singular simple present concretizes, present participle concretizing, simple past and past participle concretized)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make concrete, substantial, real, or tangible; to represent or embody a concept through a particular instance or example.
examples: An essence exists if and only if it is actualized or concretized somehow, in some concrete form.

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To be embodied, to have physical representation.
